know this is the right thing.

562
00:32:21,690 --> 00:32:22,940
We need a blood sample.

563
00:32:23,025 --> 00:32:25,610
We gotta do the
anticentromere antibody test.

564
00:32:25,694 --> 00:32:28,446
It'll show House is right.
It's scleroderma.

565
00:32:28,530 --> 00:32:30,656
Why are you doing this now?

566
00:32:31,033 --> 00:32:33,701
Because I didn't
want to kill him.

567
00:32:33,785 --> 00:32:36,954
And you're right.
I have to take a side.

568
00:32:37,831 --> 00:32:40,750
So I'm gonna do what I
can to keep him alive.

569
00:32:42,377 --> 00:32:44,253
I'll get you the blood.

570
00:32:46,381 --> 00:32:48,507
Positive for
anticentromere antibodies.

571
00:32:48,592 --> 00:32:50,051
We gotta get him
off the anti-fungals

572
00:32:50,135 --> 00:32:51,552
and onto steroids immediately.

573
00:32:51,637 --> 00:32:52,970
I told you before.

574
00:32:53,055 --> 00:32:55,556
This only points to scleroderma.
It doesn't prove it.

575
00:32:55,641 --> 00:32:57,183
You're just gonna
ignore the test?

576
00:32:57,267 --> 00:32:59,352
Blasto still fits best.

577
00:32:59,436 --> 00:33:01,020
I know it's not conclusive,
but when you put it

578
00:33:01,104 --> 00:33:02,146
with all the other evidence...

579
00:33:02,230 --> 00:33:04,565
I've made my decision.

580
00:33:10,781 --> 00:33:13,616
Have you told Thirteen
you were wrong to fire her?

581
00:33:13,700 --> 00:33:16,369
What does that have
to do with anything?

582
00:33:16,453 --> 00:33:18,871
I've worked with you long enough
to know you're reasonable.

583
00:33:18,955 --> 00:33:22,083
You can usually admit
when you're wrong.

584
00:33:22,167 --> 00:33:24,210
But there's some
deep part of you

585
00:33:24,294 --> 00:33:25,544
that when you find
you're wrong about

586
00:33:25,629 --> 00:33:28,381
the most important
decisions you've made,

587
00:33:28,465 --> 00:33:31,217
you get insecure
and you just retrench.

588
00:33:31,718 --> 00:33:33,511
If you wanna mess up your
relationship that's your right,

589
00:33:33,595 --> 00:33:36,222
but you mess this up,
our patient dies.

590
00:33:42,270 --> 00:33:44,271
Switch him to steroids.

591
00:33:54,282 --> 00:33:55,783
Hi, honey.

592
00:33:58,620 --> 00:34:00,162
How was your day?

593
00:34:05,085 --> 00:34:06,335
Morning.

594
00:34:07,838 --> 00:34:10,506
First of all, my bad.

595
00:34:11,299 --> 00:34:13,435
I've gone through this
whole thing recently.

596
00:34:13,448 --> 00:34:15,594
I don't want to bore you.

597
00:34:15,679 --> 00:34:19,515
Short version, I'm really trying
to do work on some stuff.

598
00:34:19,599 --> 00:34:22,601
This is a definite setback.

599
00:34:23,311 --> 00:34:27,398
Although, in fairness, you
really did make it tough.

600
00:34:28,692 --> 00:34:31,402
Phantom pain in
your missing arm,

601
00:34:32,654 --> 00:34:36,365
the five different kinds of
painkiller in your medicine cabinet,

602
00:34:36,450 --> 00:34:41,370
that's what this magic box of
neurological trickery is for.

603
00:34:43,790 --> 00:34:47,668
This'll be a lot easier if you do what
the crazy guy who tied you up says.

604
00:34:53,008 --> 00:34:56,093
Put your hand in there.
Put your hand in there.

605
00:34:59,556 --> 00:35:00,890
Now look.

606
00:35:01,767 --> 00:35:03,267
Mirror magic.

607
00:35:03,894 --> 00:35:05,519
Your arm is back.

608
00:35:06,354 --> 00:35:09,440
Now clench both your
fists at the same time.

609
00:35:09,524 --> 00:35:12,067
Clench. Real hard.

610
00:35:18,158 --> 00:35:20,034
If you believe in God,

611
00:35:21,369 --> 00:35:23,537
pray that this is gonna work.

612
00:35:25,165 --> 00:35:28,626
You might also want to ask him
why he blew off your arm.

613
00:35:29,336 --> 00:35:30,544
Ready?

614
00:35:32,047 --> 00:35:33,547
Now let go.

615
00:35:46,436 --> 00:35:47,812
Oh, my God.

616
00:35:48,939 --> 00:35:50,314
You relaxed it.

617
00:35:50,398 --> 00:35:54,860
For 36 years I've been in
pain, and it's finally gone.

618
00:35:55,237 --> 00:35:57,029
Oh, my God.

619
00:36:04,454 --> 00:36:05,913
Thank you.

620
00:36:08,375 --> 00:36:09,750
O2 sat's down to 88.

621
00:36:09,835 --> 00:36:13,337
Going through the main stem
bronchus into the right upper lobe.

622
00:36:13,421 --> 00:36:15,005
Get them out of here! No!

623
00:36:15,090 --> 00:36:16,090
It's okay.

624
00:36:16,174 --> 00:36:17,466
Bleeder.

625
00:36:17,551 --> 00:36:18,926
Cauterizing.

626
00:36:20,387 --> 00:36:21,887
Got it? Yeah.

627
00:36:27,519 --> 00:36:29,019
Get the paddles.

628
00:36:29,104 --> 00:36:30,145
I'm going back in.

629
00:36:30,230 --> 00:36:31,230
What is happening?

630
00:36:31,273 --> 00:36:32,982
He's bleeding into his lungs.
Charging.

631
00:36:33,066 --> 00:36:34,859
Another bleeder. I can get it.

632
00:36:34,943 --> 00:36:37,278
Hold on. There's a third.

633
00:36:39,447 --> 00:36:41,282
God, there's a dozen.

634
00:36:42,242 --> 00:36:43,534
Shock him.

635
00:36:43,618 --> 00:36:44,785
Clear.

636
00:36:48,039 --> 00:36:49,832
Charging. Clear.

