00:37:40,550 --> 00:37:43,135
You want to curl up and cry,

638
00:37:43,219 --> 00:37:45,554
the lounge chair's
a little more comfy.

639
00:37:45,639 --> 00:37:47,431
I switched his meds.

640
00:37:48,224 --> 00:37:51,226
I thought I was wrong, so I
took him off the antifungals,

641
00:37:51,311 --> 00:37:53,604
put him on steroids
like you said.

642
00:37:53,688 --> 00:37:55,981
You know what that means.

643
00:37:56,066 --> 00:38:00,361
I was too late or I was
right in the first place.

644
00:38:03,365 --> 00:38:06,450
So, either you killed him

645
00:38:06,534 --> 00:38:09,328
by not having confidence
in your opinion

646
00:38:10,705 --> 00:38:14,124
or you killed him by being too
attached to your opinion.

647
00:38:14,209 --> 00:38:17,169
If you're anything like me,
and by the way, you are,

648
00:38:17,253 --> 00:38:19,838
you need to know which.

649
00:38:19,923 --> 00:38:22,508
He's under lock and key
in the morgue.

650
00:38:22,592 --> 00:38:25,552
His government wants their own
doctors to do the autopsy.

651
00:38:25,637 --> 00:38:28,472
They're taking his body
out tomorrow.

652
00:38:28,556 --> 00:38:30,724
There's a reason I hired you.

653
00:38:32,936 --> 00:38:36,021
You used to know what to
do with a locked door.

654
00:38:44,531 --> 00:38:47,741
I went down to the morgue
to rerun the antibodies test.

655
00:38:47,867 --> 00:38:49,159
You ran it twice.

656
00:38:49,244 --> 00:38:51,495
Turns out, I couldn't get in.

657
00:38:51,579 --> 00:38:52,705
They had an armed guard.

658
00:38:53,790 --> 00:38:55,374
But I saw this.

659
00:38:59,504 --> 00:39:02,089
It's a sign-in sheet
from the morgue.

660
00:39:02,590 --> 00:39:06,176
Your signature,
9:45 this morning.

661
00:39:06,261 --> 00:39:08,262
That's right before
you guys ran the test.

662
00:39:10,098 --> 00:39:12,141
What were you doing there?

663
00:39:12,767 --> 00:39:14,018
Follow-up on a clinic case.

664
00:39:14,102 --> 00:39:15,352
What case?

665
00:39:15,437 --> 00:39:16,478
You think this is
really important?

666
00:39:16,563 --> 00:39:17,980
One of the patients
in the morgue

667
00:39:18,064 --> 00:39:20,941
was a 70-year-old woman
who had scleroderma.

668
00:39:22,235 --> 00:39:25,529
You and Cameron, if you
took that woman's blood,

669
00:39:25,613 --> 00:39:27,448
you could have
messed up the test results

670
00:39:27,532 --> 00:39:30,784
so we treated Dibala
for the wrong disease.

671
00:39:33,038 --> 00:39:35,539
Cameron had nothing
to do with it.

672
00:39:36,082 --> 00:39:37,249
You son of a bitch!

673
00:39:37,333 --> 00:39:39,835
He was going to
kill the Sitibi,

674
00:39:41,129 --> 00:39:42,171
every last one of them.

675
00:39:42,255 --> 00:39:44,381
I don't care what
he was gonna do.

676
00:39:44,466 --> 00:39:47,634
